inn1.comm: and a sign of swing first up brings a nervy prob from Vincent, it was very full and swung away
slightly wider, more swing and Vincent opts to shoulder arms
perfect outswinger, and Vincent is beaten as he produces another iffy defensive shot...he's batting from memory here
this time he's late on another very full delivery which goes under the bat as Vincent tries to drive
huge appeal, shoulders arms, the ball strikes him on the front pad and that as an incredibly close shout...Vincent doesn't know where his first run is coming from
thick inside edge into the leg side and square leg prevents the run and keeps the pressure on Vincent
comes onto the front foot and plays comfortably into the covers
gentle medium pace, outside off stump and Fleming lets in go through
played on the walk, punched back to Bhatti who fields in his follow through
comes across his stumps, takes the pad and goes backward of square on the leg side to put the pressure back on Vincent
swings into the pads, it's a run but doesn't go to Vincent's account as he stays on zero
on off stump, played into the covers, tight start from Bhatti

at last! Vincent opens his World account and in some style as plants his front foot down the pitch, swings hard and sends the ball high over cover. It carries all the way...that'll be a weight off his shoulders
this time he isn't as convincing as he tries to cut but doesn't make contact
too wide this time and an easy call for the umpire, still some swing for Cummins
tighter line and Vincent lets it go
nice ball, just outside off stump and draws Vincent into another push and the ball zips past the edge
full, swinging away, and again left to the keeper
another leave from Vincent, but he still doesn't look anywhere near his best
outside off stump, easy leave
keeps a tight line and Fleming again shoulders arms
on the stumps and Fleming is away as he turns it behind square on the leg side
shaped back into Vincent, takes the pad first and there's a half an appeal but no one was that interested...nice movement, though, from Bhatti
flicked to mid on and a fumble by Davison at mid on allows a single...not a good example from the skipper
angled down to backward point
and that's a beauty, angling into Vincent then moving away off the seam and it draws the shot and flies past the edge
wider this time and it can be comfortably left alone
another leave from Vincent, it seems to be all or nothing from him at the moment
and again as Cummins continues to probe away outside off stump, surely it can't be long until Vincent has a go at one of these
onto the front foot, takes the outside edge but played with soft hands and down to third man
driven firmly back to Cummins who does well to bend down in his follow through to collect
Fleming frees his arms and back-cuts this down to third man, he keeps the strike
full half volley, Fleming drills through the line of the ball and sends it racing through the covers...it was in the air but no one had a chance of getting near it
opts to leave this one which is a touch wider
good length, on off stump, Fleming plays from the crease back to the bowler
Fleming uses his feet and walks at Bhatti, but all he can do is nudge into the leg side
big shout, Vincent swings across the line as this one comes into him, takes the pad but going down the leg side
onto the front foot, played into the covers
firmly on-driven to mid on
short, goes for the pull but misses out, it strikes him on the body and falls down onto the pitch
onto the front foot to this one which was on off stump, takes a thick inside half of the bat into the leg side
angled across Fleming who lets it go
driven up to mid off, but Davison is on his heels and it's a well-judged single by Fleming
oversteps and Vincent frees his arms and carves over mid off, not out of the middle and it pulls up short of the fence
back of a length, pushed into the covers
overpitched from Bhatti and Fleming strokes through the line off the front foot and it threads the gap between cover and mid off...fielder is kept interested but loses the race
touch of extra bounce from this once, Fleming lets it go
too wide this time as Bhatti tries hard not to stray onto the legs
Fleming shuffles across his stumps and works this straight down the ground past mid on, superb bit of batting as he picked the gaps in the fielder after Davison has strengthened the off side
straying to far outside off stump again
tighter to the off stump and Fleming leaves
hint of movement into Fleming who leaves again
leaves again and is struck on the pad, Bhatti appeals but the ball hadn't done enough
played into the covers
decides to leave well alone, less swing now than when play started
on the stumps, Vincent comes half forward and plays down to mid on
another leave as Cummins stays on off stump
nice delivery, on off stump and brings Vincent forward, takes the outside edge and goes down to third man
angles across Fleming who leaves to end the over
started on leg stump and swung further down the leg side
full and Vincent swings through the line but without much timing, ball flies square through point and is well chased down by Geoff Barnett...still not much middle from Vincent
gentle pace outside off stump, Fleming comes onto the front foot and leaves
uses his feet, comes across the pitch and swings out to deeps square leg
good length, on off stump, Vincent drawn forward and again takes the edge down to third man
angled out to point
Fleming uses his feet....then leaves and there's a fumble from Bagai behind the stumps
bit shout for LBW but that one didn't come back well enough and they scamper the leg bye
Vincent is cheeky as you like, which is very cheeky as it happens, moving from right outside off to sweep that back through the 45. Naughty boy
outside off and that swings away... and away some more
on off, short and the batsman comes down the track, pinging that off his legs to midwicket, the fifty up for New Zealand now
swings away down off again and that's just to say wide
more banana action, but still wide enough for the batsman to leave easily enough outside off
poked into the cover region and there's a quick, but easy, single
staying over the wicket for the righthander and this over closes, at last, with a skew away off the back foot behind point. Easy pickings for the Kiwis out there
left-armer to lefthander there, and that's on off and a touch short and it's squeezed to point
pitched straight and there's a hint of drift into the righthander, allowing him to get over the ball and work that one to midwicket
came from wide of the wicket there to angle that in at the lefthander who defends over it, standing tall
not a great start, wide down leg, Fleming leaves it and it's so wide it evades the keeper
leans out and into the cover drive off a wideish one
outside off and that comes right back off the seam in at the righthander, tucking him up, and he defends tidily enough
defended into the covers
oh dear, let's call that one a loosener shall we, very loose down leg
slightly corrected line, that one on leg at least this time and it's tucked off the hips to square
left alone outside off, the ball arcing away a tad and the batsman rising on to his back foot
on leg and that's flicked up in the air, didn't get hold of that one, but it falls into space - a deliberate steer
oh, testing and tempting the fielder at wide mid-on there, but that was just too wide for him, and it runs on to the boundary
off the back foot and Vincent throws his hands at the ball, a show of aggression, there and that races away through cover this time
good comeback, on off, and that's defended forward
short and with width and that's gift-wrapped... it's unwrapped and sent flying behind point
opens the stance, walks into that one, jinking it off the toes
defended forward
that one goes across the lefthander and that's left alone as it moves away from him, the keeper takes the bails off just for fun
dabbed down to gully, a hint of hesitation from the batsmen, and that's rocketed back in with a quick arm - but the runner is in safe
pops up a touch outside off and that's left alone
bustles in with intent and flings that one down as hard as possible, but it hardly races through, slinking on to the keeper outside the off stick
banged in again, but short, and that's well struck off the back foot through cover
help yourself, Fleming down on one knee and a wide half-volley gets the inevitable treatment
outside off and that's nibbled into the covers off the back foot
placement is impeccable once more, this time a drive through extra cover

short, high and Fleming's hooked that one into the boundary boards. The trap was sprung, in theory, the man was out there at deep midwicket, but he would need go-go-Gadget arms to pluck that one on the boundary
defended into the short midwicket area
short, wide, and the batsman squats into that one, which he sends crashing off the back foot behind point
good delivery, defended quietly into the short cover region this time
reverse swept to short fine leg
left alone outside off and the batsman shoulders arms
scampered through and that's a better throw this time from Davison down in the gully - but the batsmen manage to get home easily enough
and he nearly does find a wicket first up, that one cutting back in from outside off and the batsman's nearly trapped trying to work that one into the leg side
on off and that pops up off the pads into the leg side
on leg and that's turned away to fine leg where it rolls slowly
over the wicket to the righthander and that one turns with a fair bit of, well, turn back into the batsman who works it into the covers
played forward this time and there's another quick single
played down off the back foot to just behind point
turns back in from outside off and that's worked to leg, a fifty for Fleming who smiles - they all count
outside off and that's guided out inside the square-leg boundary
flayed through point
on one knee and that's swept out to the man inside the square-leg boundary
tickled off the front foot square again and the strike's rotated once more
defended this time
comes forward and sweeps that behind square
slashed through long-off with an aerial drive
worked into the midwicket region
oops
tickled off the front foot into midwicket, and they come back for the second after a misfield and that's his fifty, his 12th in one-dayers
pitches on off and would have gone on to miss leg, but the batsman swept that into square
left alone outside off
driven through cover and that's just-to-say stopped inside the boundary
on leg and that's squeezed off the front foot through midwicket
on off this time and that's defended on the front foot
outside off, the batsman comes forward to drive, it's clean enough, but straight to the man at mid-off
glanced well off the front foot square
went for the sweep and an edge cannoned into his helmet before falling down
nearly invents a new shot, there, the crouching drive, dinking that through covers from, yes, a crouching position
nudged to square leg
with the spin, into the leg side
bat and pad together, into the off side
again, nothing going as Davison keeps a steady line
tickled into the leg side
off the back foot, into the covers and another easy single for this pair
turned with the angle through square leg
on off stump, played with very soft hands towards backward point and short third man cleans up
the breakthrough! Fleming tried to use his feet to get to the pitch and flicked the ball low towards short midwicket, nicely bowled by Sandher and well taken, low down, by Billcliff
drives handsomely first ball, big stride towards the ball and swings through the line but picks out cover
lets this one go
another leave as Fulton gets his eye in...a successful over for Canada
moves across the crease and flicks with the spin out to deep midwicket
comes forward, played under his nose and Bagai fields from behind the stumps
punched firmly back to the bowler
tries to flick this away but takes an outside edge into the off side
again onto the front foot to drive, doesn't find the middle and Davison fields in his follow through
turned to midwicket, Fulton still to open his account
short and well cut away from Vincent, he picked the gap between point and backward point and with enough power to beat the cover sweeper...he's looking much more comfortable now
back to the bowler
now he brings out the sweep but finds short fine-leg
down to short fine-leg
ooh, a play and miss from Fulton as he tries to drive
pushed wide of mid off and he gets his first World Cup run
Fulton opens up for the first time and drives with power past mid off, in the air for a while but very safe in the end
this time Davison tries to drag his length back and Fulton rocks back to cut, not a great effort to field that by short third-man and it races away
fires this in a little quicker, defended
turned from outside off stump through square leg
very full, dug out down to long off
drifting onto the pads and flicked out to deep backward square, all very easy for New Zealand
comes in with the arm and chopped to backward point
full on the stumps, worked down to long on
slightly shorter and worked with the wrists out to deep backward square
just a block from Vincent and it rolls down to long off, very sedate at the moment in the middle
full and dug out back to the bowler
almost a low full toss and the batsman misses out, bobbles back down the pitch
uses his feet, but yorks himself and fires it back to Davison
shorter this time and works with the spin into the leg side
outside off stump, onto the front foot and dab towards short third man...well taken single
flighted from Davison and tucked through midwicket
flicked in the air onto the on side but falls short of a diving midwicket...Fulton would have been annoyed to throw away his wicket there, a big score is on offer
knocked down to long on
his first ball is left alone
drawn onto the front foot, pushed to square cover
after two sighters Vincent brings out the sweep, connects well and beats deep square-leg into the fence...it was top edged a little, but still enough bat on it
defended back to Dhaniram
dropped into the leg side, scampered single
short and punched off the back foot, Dhaniram misses it and the ball goes to long off
goes over cover and with the power, Fulton extends his arms and swings through a full half volley and no one had a chance of stopping that
flicked out to deep midwicket
a similar shot by Vincent, I'll need to come up with some new words soon
off the front foot to cover
worked down to long on and very well placed just wide of the fielder and they can come back for a second...it doesn't take Fulton many strides to complete a run
helped to midwicket who makes a tumbling save
Vincent brings out  a cheeky reverse sweep, well played and he barely touched that ball but it raced away
a dinky shot to short fine-leg, yep, it's another single
that's big, onto the roof of the stand at deep midwicket as Fulton goes down on one knee and heaves this away into the area taken up by a group of school kids
this is fuller and quicker, Fulton stays tall and flicks out to square leg
a defensive shot as Vincent puts bat and pad together
easily guided out to deep square leg
on off stump and punched firmly to cover
slapped into the off side, fielded on the bounce by point who throws the stumps at the bowler's end with a direct hit, Geoff Barnett it was, but Vincent's safely home
driven out to deep cover
defended to cover
turned to mid on, who is in the circle but can't stop the single
worked to mid and it's a well judged single
driven out to long-on and they come back well for the second
that doesn't really get up on the pitch and the batsman stands tall, but has to readjust to play that one back down on the back foot
easy sweep down Easy Street AKA fine leg
defended forward this time
on one knee and that's swept tidily to square
stands tall and pushes that, no more, to mid-on
pulled away in front of midwicket, for a quick single
short, the batsman stands tall, and drives that cleanly to cover
on leg and that's tucked to long leg (and not deep leg as I tiredly typed just then)
short, outside off, and that's driven through cover
defended forward this time
on off and that's driven to cover for a quick single
worked into covers off the back foot
short and worked off the back foot into the covers
swept round to fine leg
timed into the off side of the back foot
off the front foot and that's played into midwicket this time
nice shot, tucked off the thighs and eased out in front of midwicket
on middle and that's defended down off the back foot
nipping back from off and that's driven into the off side
nipped back in from off again and that's driven into the covers
on off and that's played down off the back foot
straight, short, and that's played off the back foot into midwicket
short, outside off, and that's worked down late to third man
looped on off and that's worked off the toes to square
quick single
Nelson strikes! Well, not specifically Nelson itself, but you know what we mean. That one angles across the righthander and would have gone on to hit leg-and-middle
short, and that's driven off the back foot to point
on off and that's defended tidily
driven into the covers
worked off the legs to the 45
driven to mid-on this time
sort and swished majestically over midwicket with a firm strike
slower ball, the batsman waits for that, and it's driven out to long-on
slower ball again, good thinking, but just back of a length and that's worked easily enough into the covers
driven to cover again
looped up onto middle and that's driven to mid-on
beautifully bowled, Sandher looking good here, that one was floated up and it's well dug out with a crunch down
unconvincing sweep, misread the delivery there

Sandher grunts like he's serving at Wimbledon with the effort of delivery, but Styris was the one to induce the oohs and aahs with a crashing cover-drive, so sweetly struck, coming forward to meet that one
driven to mid-on for the solitary single this time
worked into the covers and the batsmen have to get back quickly there
short and clubbed away through midwicket, just too short and that's taken from off, see you later
eek, dragged short and Styris just drives that one through cover
four as soon as it left the hand, never mind the bat, and that's cover-driven through, cover
short and that one's biffed in front of midwicket. Given six first up, but adjusted to a four with the benefit of replays

Bagai does very well to cling on to that one in the end. He lost it in the sun, despite some big Fly-type sunnies allegedly assisting him, as Styris shot that high and higher, straight up and Bagai had to run forward and, at the last minute, dive forward to - like removing a nice apple soufflÃ© from the oven - cling on with the big gloves

Vincent faced as they crossed and he looked to have dragged that one, but in fact it clattered into the ground off an inside edge and bounced off the keeper's pads back onto the stumps. Vincent was well in his crease
worked into midwicket off the legs
"We've got him," lies the keeper as that's driven to cover, thrown tidily enough back, but the batsman was in his crease
swept to fine leg
short of a length past cover
driven to long-on
over cover but without much timing
great placment, McMillan waited for that and crunched it through cover with such timing that long off couldn't get round to it
cut away through point
tucked to short fine-leg

great catch! McMillan opened his front leg to give himself room and launched it high towards deep midwicket, but he was hitting against the breeze and the ball held up in the air...Samad ran in from the fence and held a superbly judged catch, making sure the ball didn't come out as he slid on the turf
the batsmen crossed, and Vincent works down to long on
tries to go into the on side but is taken on the pad, Davison screams an appeal but nobody else is that bothered
swept powerfully and with excellent placement, deep square-leg was only a matter of metres away but hardly set off running before the ball crossed the rope
punched to long on with a straight bat
can't beat the man at midwicket
this time short fine-leg stops Oram getting a run
works it past midwicket and with placement which allows him back for a couple
comes forward, takes a thick inside edge to midwicket
turned to midwicket
uses his feet, gets to the pitch and punches to long on
short and forced with a straight bat off the back foot down to long on

there's his century, tucked out to deep midwicket and Vincent recovers from his two ducks with a neat century. It may only be against Canada but they all count, and Vincent will be a mighty relieved man to get his run-scoring going
tries to sweep, taken on the front pad

what a strange dismissal, a loopy offspinner from Davison dips as it arrives at Vincent who tries to work through midwicket - having started to think about the sweep - and got a leading edge which gently lobbed back to Davison
worked down to long on, McCullum is quick and easily makes it back for a second
can't get this one past midwicket
tucked into the leg side
and again from Oram, midwicket being kept busy
played into the pitch and bounces down to long on
solidly played to cover
driven softly to cover
uses his wrists to flick this down to long on
slightly short and McCullum plays a flat-bat pull to long on
Oram continues his sedate start with a forward defensive
uses his feet this time, gets to the pitch, but picks out cover
slight wider, Oram lofts this over Geoff Barnett at long off with just one hand on the bat...that shows the power of the allrounder, maybe that will get Oram going
worked from outside off stump out to midwicket
down the track again from Oram, but keeps the ball along the deck this time to long off
brings out the reverse sweep but goes straight to short third man
swung high and handsome by McCullum, goes down on one knee and slog sweeps onto the roof of the stand which Fulton picked out earlier in the day
pushed out to deep square-leg, the shot was well paced and they make it back for a brace...300 up for the second innings in a row

that's helped over the rope by Cummins at long on for another six. McCullum swung hard at it, but sent it with more height than distance but Cummins could only palm it over the fence...shame, Sandher bowled a decent spell
crunched down the track but it strikes McCullum's bat and rebounds down to long off for just a single
flicked out to deep backward square, McCullum feels he could have got that finer for four
good yorker, dug out down to long on
unlucky for Cummins, full delivery on leg stump and a thin inside edge races down to fine leg for a boundary...that's the hazard of bowling at the death
another excellent yorker, this time just squeezed out to square leg
low full toss carved through the covers and out to the sweeper
full ball, swung down to long
full toss and that was asking to be hit, which it was, a long way over square for another six
tries it again, but that ball pitches and McCullum misses, taken on the body
uses his feet, makes it into a yorker and worked to long on, well bowled
goes for another swing over the leg side, takes a leading edge and loops to where mid off would have been...but he's down on the fence
flicks this down the ground, in the air but drops just short of long on...50 partnership off just 30 balls, good hitting
well bowled slower ball, swung hard into the leg side
lofted out towards deep midwicket, another brace for McCullum
laced with one hand down to long on
gets underneath this one and lofts into the off side, again the ball falls short of the fielder - this time deep cover running in
turned through midwicket, Cummins doing a fair job at the death
low full toss and awesome power from Oram who launches it straight down the ground for another maximum
the crowd at deep midwicket gets more catching practice as McCullum launches his favourite slog-sweep over the boundary...again

uses his feet this time, Oram comes back for a second and the TV umpire is called in...the reactions suggest he's save and the pictures confirm it...although only by a couple of inches, but that's enough
it's the leg side again! that's the fastest ever World Cup fifty, just 20 balls of brilliant striking from McCullum who has added a fine flourish to the innings
swung with one hand out to deep square leg

now it's Oram's turn...this one almost goes out of the ground and would probably after cleared the boundary at the MCG as he goes inside out over extra cover...it was wind-assisted but still some blow
the final ball is dug out towards midwicket to complete an explosive, and ultra-professional innings by New Zealand

inn2.comm: clattered into the pad on leg and there's an attempted rush into the leg side
off the mark this time with one which is eased out off the legs in front of midwicket
short, and taken from off and moved into the leg side in front of midwicket
a touch short and that's square-driven off the front foot to point
short and that's typical Davison - a good, clean strike over midwicket
down the wicket and scythed away through third man, an outside edge flies thickly and quickly away, not where he wanted that to go, but that will go
rushed over the outside edge as the batsman shapes to leave it outside off
defended forward this time
defended forward
driven to point
on leg and that's worked behind square - the batsmen set off, yes, no, yes, no, and decide no... but in truth it could have been yes if they had gone first time
bowled him, just too quick and that's a no-ball - Davison gives a big grin as that one clatters right into his middle stump, cleaned up a treat, but gets another life
nips back from off, but a touch short and the batsman has room to play that down off the back foot to point
hustles in to bowl and there's a huge shout - a valid one - from the bowler, but the umpire turns it down
brings his bat down late and doesn't get the shape of the drive quite right, aiming for mid-off, but that's driven out to cover instead
on off, a touch short, and that's worked off the legs just in front of midwicket
across the lefthander, on a straightish line, and that's on middle and worked out in front of midwicket
oh, a good delivery, across the lefthander again and induces him into a false stroke, feeling for that one outside the off stump on the front foot
accurate again from Tuffey and that's stunned into the covers
got on top of the bounce there and that races away for four through point off the back foot
short and wide that's timed all the way to the fence, this time that's off the back foot and the base of the bat, and that rockets behind point
on leg and that's another four! This one flies away behind square and the crowd go wild
hello! Lovely. This one is a front-foot sweet smash through mid-off, another clean strike and you've got to be happy with that one
oversteps and Davison steps over and flamingo-whips that in front of midwicket, but without much timing this time
good response from Mason, slower ball drifting in on leg, and that drifts in too much
slower again, short, wide down leg and Davison pulls that easily away
ooh, desperate - and yet confident - appeal from New Zealand for a fine edge through from one which swung away, but he missed it by a long way
short, on middle and that one's struck strongly out of the middle of the bat and Tuffey is suddenly, erm, huffy. Well, he is
driven to cover
rockets away off the toes and that's Canada's fifty. The crowd are loving this, Fleming, double-teapotting, is emphatically not. 30 balls for that fifty!
defended on the back foot and the crowd jeers as Tuffey tries to run out Barnett, who's out of his crease
short, straighter and that's squeezed to midwicket. Barnett steals the strike
on off and that's defended forward
on leg and that's scampered through off the hips - Canada need to keep rotating the singles where possible and putting the pressure on New Zealand
half-volley, driven out to the man at cover
short and smashed! Crackerjack, as Mark Nicholas would say, meated out of the middle with a corking cover-drive that's travelling
drives that one straight into the ground this time into the covers and can't get that one away

top stuff. Davison came down the track to meet that one, short and outside off, and he creams it through cover, bisecting the two men in the process. Oh, wash your mouth out Mr Mason, there are lipreading children watching
driven to the man at cover who desperately chucks the ball back in at the non-striker's end, Davison backing up like an excitable rabbit, but he had scampered back to his crease
short and defended on the back foot into the covers
driven to cover and Vettori just got a finger tip to it to take the pace off the ball with his dive from mid-on
a wide down leg
angles that across the lefthander, it veering to the off stick, where it's defended tidily forward
overstepped, that ball is straight again and that's driven straight to the man at cover
slower ball, short, and that's timed out to the man at square, but without much power
short and that flashes past the outside edge of a wafting Barnett, almost trapped in his crease, there
knee-high full toss and Davison snicks that one through fine leg. Fifty from 23 deliveries and he beats his previous fastest fifty. Well batted
looked to be the shot of the day there, a straight drive, but wasn't quite timed in fact, and New Zealand did have a man in the deep to cut that one off
played straight off the back foot
nearly inside-edged that one behind square
slower ball and there's a throaty roar which sounded a bit like "Ooohaahharr", which translates as "Howzat" of course, but that was crashing into the leg, and would have gone on down leg. No cigar
Davison miscues to midwicket this time
dropped! That was nearly the wicket they needed. McCullum should have pouched that one - a decent take to a thick outside edge, diving frog-like to his left with two hands and he shells it
driven into the covers
tickled off the legs, square
well bowled, and well played forward over that one, Davison bringing down his bat on it quickly to stun the yorker in its infancy - and they squeeze out a run
wider from outside off, a decent length, and that's defended back to the bowler
outside off and that's defended down with a straight bat
slower delivery, defended this time
overstepped and that's worked softly to square
taken from outside off, unconvincing whack into the short midwicket region
slower ball, full, and Davison's bottom hand flies up off the bat in trying to drive that straight and back past the bowler

got him! That's the blow. Mason's face is an absolute picture of delight as Davison's rout comes to an end. A short ball, Davison tried to target the leg side and didn't get the middle of the bat, Mason standing firm to take a solid catch
squeezed into midwicket
short and that's nibbled forward in defence
short and wide, too wide in fact, and a whoosh from Barnett
tucked to midwicket off middle stump
pushed out to cover, another direct hit from Vincent but the batsman wasn't going anywhere
forced off the back foot to cover
ooh, that man Vincent is in the action again as a flashing cover drive races past him for four...he actually got a finger trip to it, but that would have been a stunning catch
straighter and played down to mid off
top shot, two steps down the track and Barnett sends that high over mid on...Davison has gone, but the attacking continues from Canada
drifting down the leg side
back of a length, forced off the back foot back to the bowler
another tight run to Vincent at cover as Bagai drops it with soft hands and sets off, a direct hit would have been gone
on middle and off, forced between midwicket and mid on
works this with good timing back down the pitch, Mason fields off his own bowling
slower ball, Barnett comes forward and it dribbles onto the leg side
Barnett down the track again, doesn't get to it and mistimes down to mid off
hits a length straight away, Bagai nearly has a nibble but lifts his bat out of the way just in time
again leaves this well alone
bat on ball this time as he forces off the back foot to square cover
draws Bagai on to the front foot this time, played out to point
